{"id": "EUVD-2022-55000", "enisaUuid": "4773abf5-96f2-357c-9238-f4182fe74017", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: asix: add proper error handling of usb read errors\n\nSyzbot once again hit uninit value in asix driver. The problem still the\nsame -- asix_read_cmd() reads less bytes, than was requested by caller.\n\nSince all read requests are performed via asix_read_cmd() let's catch\nusb related error there and add __must_check notation to be sure all\ncallers actually check return value.\n\nSo, this patch adds sanity check inside asix_read_cmd(), that simply\nchecks if bytes read are not less, than was requested and adds missing\nerror handling of asix_read_cmd() all across the driver code.", "datePublished": "2025-10-21T12:31:23", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-21T12:31:23", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b96a7265f763b37ff3138b9ca8122a950f13b00e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9ea8d2fca8fea3b17005b4dc02f8ef15f7a2fb97", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/662ff765470ad0d11a1153d6d8e99d69a98e60b4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/920a9fa27e7805499cfe78491b36fed2322c02ec", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49226"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49226"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0dfd4712-1758-3f8e-b3ca-e2f036e03965", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d9fe64e511144c1ee7d7555b4111f09dde9692ef <662ff765470ad0d11a1153d6d8e99d69a98e60b4"}, {"id": "2358cbad-df53-3160-a3ac-766b16cd45ae", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.2"}, {"id": "331e7a18-ca34-32a2-83b6-e774c279daba", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.33"}, {"id": "40a7df94-84b9-3bd6-98dc-f59659ec2150", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}, {"id": "67f1f2cd-9cc6-33d4-8a20-26ff7a8dd00e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d9fe64e511144c1ee7d7555b4111f09dde9692ef <920a9fa27e7805499cfe7849